  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Banque Internationale pour le Commerce et l&apos;Industrie de la Guinee</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project is for an up to GNF 17.5 billion Risk Sharing Facility to support SME lending in post conflict Guinea for Banque Internationale pour le Commerce et lIndustrie de la Guin&#xE9;e (BICIGUI or the Bank), a subsidiary of BNP Paribas. As of December 31st, 2012, BICIGUI was the largest bank in the country banking sector in terms of loans (25%) and first in terms of deposits (27%) and assets (23%), with a network of 24 branches in 15 cities. Created in 1985, the Bank operates a universal bank business model servicing the retail, SME and corporate business segments.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is expected to have significant development impact by: i)	Promoting lending to viable SMEs in a fragile, post conflict environment where access to finance is difficult; ii)	Supporting  local entrepreneurs, in particular SMEs, which are important contributors to job creation.; iii)    Helping to improve the E&amp;S assessment and mitigation management system of a leading bank in the country.</narrative>
  </description>
